nib.text:
Firefighters extinguished a house fire in Longfellow Tuesday afternoon, officials said. 

At around 2 p.m., firefighters responded to a report of a house fire in the 2900 block of 32nd Avenue S.

Upon arrival, crews discovered a 1 and a half story home had caught fire and immediately began working to extinguish the blaze which had spread outside the home.

After several minutes of attack, the outside fire was extinguished and crews began working on the fire inside the home which had spread through the roof. 

At around 4 p.m., the MFD reported the bulk of the fire had been extinguished after crews had ventilated the roof. 

One firefighter sustained a shoulder injury and was taken to the hospital for evaluation. No other injuries were reported and all occupants were evacuated. 

The house was deemed uninhabitable and the eight residents (including 3 children) are being assisted by the Red Cross. 

Investigators are determining the cause of the blaze.
